miscConds.notes: The defendant shall not commit any criminal offenses; shall notify the Taylor County District Attorney's Office, as well as the Clerk of Court's office, of any change of address within ten days of said change. judgments.dispoDesc: Pursuant to an agreement the court granted the state's motion for a deferred entry of judgment of conviction on this charge for a period of on year.  Upon successful completion of the agreement the state will move to dimiss this charge.

Defendant Kaia R. Starr in court with attorney Karl J. Kelz.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Plea agreement put into the record.  Written waiver of preliminary hearing filed with the court. Defendant freely and voluntarily waives right to a preliminary hearing.    Court binds defendant over for  trial.  Information filed.  Waive reading of Information.  Plea of no contest to count 1 and the amended count 2.    Count 2 is amended to Possession of Controlled Substance 961.41(3g)(b).   Plea colloquy.  Plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently; factual basis exists.  Court orders in count 1 a deferred entry of judgment for one year.  Court signs Order for Deferred Agreement.   Court finds defendant guilty of Count 2.  Court orders in Count 2 a withheld sentence and probation for one year with the conditions of court costs; DNA surcharge; no contact with JH, RH, AK, TA or GP; counseling as deemed appropriate by probation; at agents discretion obtain GED/HSED or adult diploma with the Medford adult diploma academy.  - rt
